139. **Decision**: He must either wear it—or burn it;  
140. **Climax**: He puts it on—and his body starts to change.  
141. **Outcome**: He burns it. The suit is gone. But the next day, a new suit appears—on his bed.  
142. **Clever twist**: The clothes don’t fit—they *become* the person;  
143. **Clever worldbuilding feature**: In this city, every suit is a soul—only the tailor can make it;  
144. **Scene**: A single stitch. A single change. A single moment of transformation.

